	1. Screen - Application and Lifestyle Screen									
	a. Widget/Sections									
	 i.      Personal Information									
	Age, height, weight (used to calculate BMI), gender, occupation, and financial information to justify the coverage amount						Included in Demo			
	ii.      Lifestyle Choices									
	Questions about tobacco/nicotine use, alcohol consumption, and hazardous hobbies, extreme sports						Included in Demo			
	iii.      Motor Vehicle Report									
	Driving history, including DUIs or reckless driving infractions, to assess risk						Not in Demo rule			
	iv.      Criminal History									
	Inquiry into felony convictions						Not in Demo rule			
	v.      Travel/Residence									
	Travel to hazardous locations or residence outside the U.S. can be a factor. 						Included in Demo			
										
										
	1. Screen - Medical and Health Screen									
	a. Widget/Sections									
	  i.      Health Questionnaire									
	      Detailed questions about medical history, current physicians, medications, family history and pre-existing conditions						Partly in Demo UW rule			
	 ii.      Medical Information Bureau (MIB) Check									
	      A check of the MIB database for past insurance applications and reported health conditions						Partly in Demo UW rule			
	iii.      Prescription Drug History									
	      Accessing prescription history reports to confirm medical conditions and adherence to treatment						Partly in Demo UW rule			
	 iv.      Medical Records 									
	      Requesting an Attending Physician's Statement (APS), which is a summary of an applicant's medical records from their doctor						Partly in Demo UW rule			
	v.   Paramedical Exam/Lab Tests - A medical professional may conduct an exam									
							Not is Demo			
										
										
